pears inside the bowl reading “tougher on stains.” The blue color deepens toward the drain area, suggesting cleaner spreading through the water. The words break apart into clusters of small white dots, which then gather and move in curved paths along the swirling blue water. Another bold white phrase appears: “tougher on odors.” Again, small white bubble-like dots arc through the bowl as the blue cleaner continues to spread and swirl.\n\nThe miniature captain reappears standing beside a blue Ty-D-Bol package and the small white model toilet bowl. The package has a bright yellow label with the Ty-D-Bol name, and the small toilet bowl is connected to tubing or a curved fixture, reinforcing the product-in-use demonstration. The captain stands upright near the product, one hand raised as if continuing to explain.\n\nThe commercial ends with two Ty-D-Bol bottles displayed side by side on a white surface, likely a toilet tank lid. Both bottles are blue with yellow caps and yellow labels. White on-screen text above the smaller bottle on the left reads, “Ty-D-bol Regular Lemon Fresh Blue with BORAX.” White text above the larger, wider bottle on the right reads, “New Ty-D-bol Economy Size with BORAX.”",
